title: Definitions
context: PART V. TRESPASS TO VESSEL [ยง200-61] Definitions. As used in this part: &ldquo;Enforcement officer&rdquo; means a police officer and any other state or county officer charged with the enforcement of state laws. &ldquo;Vessel&rdquo; means every description of watercraft used or capable of being used as a means of transportation on water. &ldquo;Waters of the State&rdquo; means any waters within the jurisdiction of the State, the marginal seas adjacent to the State, and the high seas when navigated as part of a journey or ride to or from the shores of the State. [L 1991, c 272, pt of ยง2]
